1685
03:36:19.175 --> 03:36:21.837
Who is Secretary Bailey?

1686
03:36:30.603 --> 03:36:34.221
Secretary Bailey is a rich businessman.

1687
03:36:39.945 --> 03:36:44.530
He came to the United States as a starving
immigrant and made a lot of money...

1688
03:36:44.742 --> 03:36:48.610
...in San Francisco and Los Angeles,
where he's lived for 30 years.

1689
03:36:48.787 --> 03:36:52.871
I know all that. It's all in the papers.
What else is there?

1690
03:36:59.381 --> 03:37:02.373
He married a very wealthy woman.

1691
03:37:03.677 --> 03:37:06.009
They had a Child.

1692
03:37:06.388 --> 03:37:08.094
She died when the child was born.

1693
03:37:10.017 --> 03:37:14.556
A few years ago, he went into politics.
Moved here.

1694
03:37:14.730 --> 03:37:19.349
That's all past history. I'm not talking
about that. I'm talking about now.

1695
03:37:19.944 --> 03:37:22.902
Right now he's in trouble.

1696
03:37:24.073 --> 03:37:27.611
Why can't you just tell me you've
been living with him all these years...

1697
03:37:27.785 --> 03:37:29.741
...and that you're his lover?

1698
03:37:38.587 --> 03:37:41.579
Age can wither me, Noodles.

1699
03:37:45.302 --> 03:37:47.918
We're both getting Old.

1700
03:37:53.269 --> 03:37:56.557
All that we have left now
are our memories.

1701
03:37:59.483 --> 03:38:04.068
If you go to that party on Saturday
night, you won't have those anymore.

1702
03:38:06.740 --> 03:38:09.277
Tear up that invitation.

1703
03:38:11.453 --> 03:38:14.286
There's an exit back this way.

1704
03:38:15.082 --> 03:38:18.119
Noodles, go through it.

1705
03:38:20.713 --> 03:38:22.544
Keep walking.

1706
03:38:22.715 --> 03:38:25.127
Don't turn around.

1707
03:38:26.260 --> 03:38:28.501
Please, Noodles.

1708
03:38:28.679 --> 03:38:31.796
I'm begging you. Please.

1709
03:38:38.272 --> 03:38:40.979
Are you afraid that I'll turn
into a pillar Of salt?

1710
03:38:45.279 --> 03:38:49.067
If you go out that door, yes.

1711
03:39:47.299 --> 03:39:50.257
DEBORAH:
This is Secretary Bailey's son.

1712
03:39:50.469 --> 03:39:53.961
His name's David, just like yours.

1713
03:41:09.548 --> 03:41:12.540
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

1714
03:41:49.296 --> 03:41:53.289
[BAND PLAYING GEORGE GERSHWIN'S
"SUMMERTIME"]

1715
03:42:22.162 --> 03:42:23.618
[O'DONNELL CHUCKLES]

1716
03:42:26.458 --> 03:42:31.873
I must admit, this party
was a wonderful idea, Mr. Secretary.

1717
03:42:32.047 --> 03:42:35.756
It's a bit like saying, "I'm going up
before the committee in five days...

1718
03:42:35.926 --> 03:42:38.292
...but my conscience is clear.

1719
03:42:38.470 --> 03:42:42.338
The most important people in New York
are my guests."

1720
03:42:42.516 --> 03:42:44.222
It's going to be a night to remember.

1721
03:42:46.061 --> 03:42:48.017
Especially if the house blows up.

1722
03:42:48.814 --> 03:42:51.021
Where are you putting the next bomb?

1723
03:42:52.526 --> 03:42:54.608
In the freezer...

1724
03:42:55.237 --> 03:42:57.523
...Or in the toilet, hm?

1725
03:43:05.247 --> 03:43:07.954
You can't even think straight anymore.

1726
03:43:09.251 --> 03:43:11.492
I'll tell you something.

1727
03:43:11.670 --> 03:43:15.413
There's a waiting list Of people
who'd like to send flowers tO your funeral.

1728
03:43:18.594 --> 03:43:20.960
I can point out 10 Of them right now,
if you'd like me tO.

1729
03:43:21.138 --> 03:43:22.674
MAX:
Yes.

1730
03:43:22.848 --> 03:43:27.808
But none of them wants to read my obituary
in front Of the committee as much as you do.

1731
03:43:27.978 --> 03:43:29.559
You and your union.

1732
03:43:33.025 --> 03:43:35.687
We just wanna resolve this situation,
clean and legal.

1733
03:43:35.861 --> 03:43:39.399
I've heard that same song from you
for 35 fucking years.

1734
03:43:39.573 --> 03:43:42.360
Who do you think you're talking to?

1735
03:43:43.660 --> 03:43:47.448
I helped you to make a fortune,
you and the rest of those parasites.

1736
03:43:47.623 --> 03:43:49.579
It was a reasonable arrangement...

1737
03:43:49.750 --> 03:43:53.288
...between labor and management.

1738
03:43:53.462 --> 03:43:57.250
Two percent for them
and 40 percent for you.

1739
03:43:57.424 --> 03:44:00.382
You defend them and you screw them.
Come on.

1740
03:44:00.928 --> 03:44:03.294
It's been the story Of your life.

1741
03:44:04.181 --> 03:44:07.594
-Think anybody believes you anymore?
-Some.

1742
03:44:08.435 --> 03:44:11.017
But no one believes in you anymore...

1743
03:44:11.188 --> 03:44:14.305
...because you've made mistakes
and I haven't.

1744
03:44:15.567 --> 03:44:18.809
But that's beside the point.

1745
03:44:20.155 --> 03:44:22.862
The important thing right now is that...

1746
03:44:23.033 --> 03:44:26.867
...you and I straighten out
these transfers Of authority.

1747
03:44:28.830 --> 03:44:31.913
Now, it's all as we've agreed.

1748
03:44:34.378 --> 03:44:37.870
I've had our lawyers draw it up.

1749
03:44:39.007 --> 03:44:41.293
All you have to do is sign.

1750
03:44:49.685 --> 03:44:52.142
My last will?

1751
03:44:53.480 --> 03:44:55.971
You're in no position tO exercise your will.

1752
03:44:58.527 --> 03:44:59.937
I give up everything.

1753
03:45:02.656 --> 03:45:04.647
Twelve percent will be set aside
for your boy.

1754
03:45:05.492 --> 03:45:07.949
That way he can be assured...

1755
03:45:08.120 --> 03:45:10.702
...Of living to a ripe old age.

1756
03:45:10.872 --> 03:45:15.206
Or not, if I don't sign. Hm?

1757
03:46:02.716 --> 03:46:06.709
[BAND PLAYING COLE PORTER'S
"NIGHT AND DAY"]

1758
03:46:24.529 --> 03:46:27.396
Why don't you
take care Of this yourself, Max?

1759
03:46:28.867 --> 03:46:30.573
I'd be very happy for you tonight if...

1760
03:46:33.413 --> 03:46:35.699
Maybe you will.

1761
03:46:51.848 --> 03:46:54.840
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

1762
03:47:45.569 --> 03:47:47.730
[DOOR OPENS]

1763
03:47:47.904 --> 03:47:49.735
BUTLER:
Please go in.

1764
03:48:04.129 --> 03:48:06.290
MAX:
What are you waiting for?

1765
03:48:10.135 --> 03:48:12.592
I don't understand, Mr. Bailey.

1766
03:48:39.289 --> 03:48:41.371
Sit down, Noodles.

1767
03:48:45.629 --> 03:48:47.415
Make yourself comfortable.

1768
03:49:05.815 --> 03:49:08.522
I'm glad you accepted my invitation.

1769
03:49:08.693 --> 03:49:10.684
Well, I was curious.

1770
03:49:13.657 --> 03:49:16.774
SO many important people in one place.

1771
03:49:16.993 --> 03:49:20.861
MAX: Yes. Well, the rats usually
desert a sinking ship.

1772
03:49:21.331 --> 03:49:25.495
But in my case, they appear to be
flocking onboard.

1773
03:49:36.888 --> 03:49:40.722
Yeah, well, I read about
your troubles in the newspapers.

1774
03:49:42.102 --> 03:49:46.766
But a man in your position, with all
your power and all your privileges...

1775
03:49:46.982 --> 03:49:51.225
...has to assume a certain amount
of responsibility...

1776
03:49:51.903 --> 03:49:54.360
...a certain amount of risk.

1777
03:50:01.830 --> 03:50:04.572
Why'd you ask me
to come here, Mr. Bailey?

1778
03:50:07.919 --> 03:50:12.413
That invitation doesn't mean
a goddamn thing, and you know it.

1779
03:50:12.799 --> 03:50:16.337
All that counts is what
was in that suitcase.

1780
03:50:18.013 --> 03:50:20.800
The money and the contract.

1781
03:50:23.560 --> 03:50:26.051
It didn't say who the contract
was on, though.

1782
03:50:28.106 --> 03:50:30.518
Haven't you figured that out yet?

1783
03:50:32.152 --> 03:50:33.767
You, Mr. Bailey?

1784
03:50:47.584 --> 03:50:51.293
I haven't had a gun in my hand
for many, many years.

1785
03:50:52.922 --> 03:50:58.462
My eyes aren't too good,
even with my glasses. My hands shake.

1786
03:51:01.348 --> 03:51:05.341
-And I wouldn't wanna miss, Mr. Bailey.
-Cut the bullshit, Noodles.

1787
03:51:06.895 --> 03:51:09.637
I'm already a dead man.

1788
03:51:10.565 --> 03:51:14.979
At least give me the chance
to settle the debt that I owe to you.

1789
03:51:15.653 --> 03:51:18.941
I'll never make it before
the investigating committee.

1790
03:51:19.115 --> 03:51:23.279
They're scared to death
I'II implicate the whole bunch Of them.

1791
03:51:23.661 --> 03:51:25.868
They gotta get rid of me.

1792
03:51:28.541 --> 03:51:31.499
Today is as good a day as any.

1793
03:51:33.671 --> 03:51:36.037
You do it, Noodles.

1794
03:51:37.008 --> 03:51:40.375
You're the only person
I can accept it from.

1795
03:51:47.102 --> 03:51:49.844
You see, I found out where you were.

1796
03:51:50.021 --> 03:51:53.104
I brought you back here for this.

1797
03:51:54.442 --> 03:51:57.650
To even the score between you and me.

1798
03:52:00.031 --> 03:52:02.488
You can get out through there.

1799
03:52:04.911 --> 03:52:09.575
[BAND PLAYING JOHN LENNON
& PAUL MCCARTNEY'S "YESTERDAY"]

1800
03:52:09.749 --> 03:52:14.288
It leads right down to the street.
Nobody will see you.

1801
03:52:21.052 --> 03:52:25.421
I don't know what you're talking about,
Mr. Bailey. You don't owe me a thing.

1802
03:52:33.398 --> 03:52:39.519
Your eyes were too full of tears to see
it wasn't me burned up on that street.

1803
03:52:40.363 --> 03:52:42.228
It was somebody else.

1804
03:52:43.825 --> 03:52:48.740
You were too shocked to realize
that the cops were in on it too.

1805
03:53:02.886 --> 03:53:05.002
You're crazy.

1806
03:53:07.348 --> 03:53:11.591
You said that to me once before,
a long time ago.

1807
03:53:11.895 --> 03:53:15.353
But my mind was never as clear
as it was at that moment.

1808
03:53:16.107 --> 03:53:19.599
I took away your whole life from you.

1809
03:53:19.819 --> 03:53:22.652
I've been living in your place.

1810
03:53:23.698 --> 03:53:26.485
I took everything.

1811
03:53:27.785 --> 03:53:30.071
I took your money.

1812
03:53:30.705 --> 03:53:32.912
I took your girl.

1813
03:53:33.625 --> 03:53:38.415
All I left for you was 35 years of grief
over having killed me.

1814
03:53:40.006 --> 03:53:41.997
Now, why don't you shoot?

1815
03:54:27.971 --> 03:54:29.962
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

1816
03:55:16.686 --> 03:55:19.598
It's true,
I have killed people, Mr. Bailey.

1817
03:55:19.814 --> 03:55:24.558
Sometimes to defend myself,
sometimes for money.

1818
03:55:24.736 --> 03:55:27.398
And many people used to come to us.

1819
03:55:27.614 --> 03:55:30.526
Business partners, rivals...

1820
03:55:30.908 --> 03:55:33.069
...Iovers.

1821
03:55:33.453 --> 03:55:37.571
Some of the jobs we took
and some we didn't.

1822
03:55:50.970 --> 03:55:53.928
Yours is one we would never touch,
Mr. Bailey.

1823
03:55:54.807 --> 03:55:56.843
Is this your way Of getting revenge?

1824
03:56:01.606 --> 03:56:03.312
NO.

1825
03:56:06.653 --> 03:56:09.770
It's just the way I see things.

1826
03:57:12.468 --> 03:57:14.379
It's 10:25...

1827
03:57:16.431 --> 03:57:19.423
...and I've got nothing left to lose.

1828
03:57:21.728 --> 03:57:25.812
When you've been betrayed by a friend,
you hit back.

1829
03:57:30.862 --> 03:57:32.693
DO it.

1830
03:57:54.677 --> 03:57:57.464
You see, Mr. Secretary...

1831
03:57:59.474 --> 03:58:01.556
...I have a story also.

1832
03:58:02.351 --> 03:58:04.558
A little simpler than yours.

1833
03:58:06.189 --> 03:58:10.899
Many years ago I had a friend,
a dear friend.

1834
03:58:12.528 --> 03:58:15.770
I turned him in to save his life...

1835
03:58:15.990 --> 03:58:18.276
...but he was killed.

1836
03:58:19.577 --> 03:58:22.410
But he wanted it that way.

1837
03:58:23.331 --> 03:58:25.663
It was a great friendship.

1838
03:58:28.753 --> 03:58:32.792
It went bad for him
and it went bad for me too.

1839
03:58:37.637 --> 03:58:39.923
Good night, Mr. Bailey.

1840
03:58:49.106 --> 03:58:52.815
I hope the investigation
turns out to be nothing.

1841
03:58:54.737 --> 03:58:58.776
It'd be a shame to see
a lifetime Of work go to waste.

1842
